						               													<description>1. Lustige Fahrt ins Schlaue&amp;#10;Each player gets 10 game token and a car to place on the starting-space. A quiz-card is placed on each grey space and a event-card on each red space. The movement of the cars is determined by a die. If a car lands on a pace neighbouring an event-card, the player has to follow the instructions printed on the card. If a car lands on a space besides a quiz-card the player has to answer the question on the card. If the answer is correct, he collects the card. All used cards are imediatly replaced by new ones.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to reach the finish space receives 6 game token, the second gets 3 token. The game ends, when the second player reaches the finsh. All token and quiz-cards count for 1 point each. The player with the most points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. Quiz-Karussell (backside of the game board)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;a) 6er-Karussell: The quiz master takes 40 quiz-cards and 10 event-cards from the deck and places 1 card on each colored space. The player rolls a die and has to answer the question on the quiz-card or follow the instruction on the event-card beside the rolled number. The player may chose betweent two permissible cards because there are two spaces for each number. The game ends, when all 50 cards have been used. Points are awarded for token and collected quiz-cards same as in the game &amp;quot;Lustige Fahrt ins Schlaue&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;b) 12er-Karussell: In this game the player rolls a die (1-6) and can't chose between two cards. If he don't knows the answer to a quiz-card he has to pay a token and roll a second time. The second result is added to the first one to determine a second card. If he can't answer the question on the second card, there is no penality involved and his turn ends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Many of the quiz- and event-cards are traffic related.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
